texts.text: >The cultists attack the Liberators all at once...!
If that's the way it's gonna be, let's dance!
>Vince's kick knocks several cultists down all at once.
You shall not interfere! Reverend, now...!
Hey, what are you...?!
Thank you, my children.
Oh, mighty Outer God. We offer this heart to thee!
Hear me! Answer my call!

Nyarl Sh'tan!
Nyarl G'shana!
>The room goes dark and a sudden gust of air erupts from the center.
>Everyone reacts by covering their faces.
>But as they look up, they see a faceless demon levitating above the altar.
Shit! We're too late!
>The cultists all raise their hands in unison and cheer.

We did it...!
It finally worked...!

Oh, blessed light...!
We shall be saved...!

*Chuckle*
Ah, pathetic humans...
>The demon begins speaking in an incomprehensible language.
Wait, how...?! I can understand it, but this language...?!
It speaks...! It's speaking directly into my mind...!
I am the god of chaos, Nyarlathotep.
Speak. What is it that you seek?
>The cult leader steps forward to answer.
We have but one wish.
Let this world drown in chaos...!
>As the leader utters his wish, the rest begin to follow.
Bring this world to its knees!
Please, quickly! I can't take it anymore!
What?! We need to stop them...!
Devil Download!
Ah, demons users. I've heard but only rumors.
To think that any would actually obey you.
Everyone, we need to fight! We can use our combo attack...!
>The worshippers then begin shouting back.
Stop! Don't interfere!
Please, run! We can't let you do this!
Shut up! You wouldn't understand!
Being born into a god-awful family!
Going to a god-awful school! Having to live in this god-awful world!
I want to just forget about this "reality"...!
God isn't going to save anyone.
But we can call to "our god". We can summon "our god".
"Our god" can do something about this world, this "reality"...
"Our god" can turn "reality" into "chaos" for us...!
Hah. And you're trying to turn this world into a living hell?
What a coincidence. I've been down that path too.
You don't look like you have. Especially since you even have a daughter.
Daughter?
I think he's pointing to me, Vince.
What?! You're joking, right? There's no way she's my kid.
Pretty close, but no cigar.
If anything, she's like my little sister...
Little sister...?
I had someone like that once...
But she ended up taking her own life because of this damn world's bullshit...
That's right. This world made her do that!
This society, this country, this world! It killed my little sister!
Ah, I see. I hoped to sit back and listen a while longer...
But is that why you called me here?
>Each word the demon utters feels like it's bringing you one step closer to madness.
>Vince somehow keeps that at bay and manages to reply.
Hah. So this demon's gonna destroy this world for you?
Yes! You just don't get it!
No, I do.
Huh...?
Anyone in your position would think the same thing.
Someone said, "Bring this world to its knees."
A younger me would've sympathized with that person.
Oh? So you're not just some snot-nosed hacker kid...?
I never knew about your past.
Enough about me.
We need to stop Nyarlathotep and send it back to wherever it came from...
Yeah, get lost!
Amen to that.
I knew it. I knew you wouldn't understand us!
That's different.
I don't give a crap about what happens to this world...
Hell, mine's already gone in a way...
Hm? But you have changed a little. Right, Vince?
Hah. Not my core. Nothing about that has changed one bit.
But I've probably been hanging out with those kids too much.
Anyways, we need to do something about Nyarlathotep!
No, you shall not!
*Grunt*
Foolish, feeble-minded humans...
Become one step closer to the truth...
This is bad! What's it going to do...?!
>Nyarlathotep points its finger to the sky and summons a hoard of demons!
*Growl*
*Hiss*
What the?!
Great, more demons...!
>Nyarlathotep begins to whisper softly.

*Snicker*
Time for you to enjoy a taste of my chaotic illusions.
>Nyarlathotep snaps its fingers.
Your human eyes will now perceive others as demons.
What?! Everyone other than us just turned into monsters...!
Look closely?
Some will remain in their human forms.
Are you okay, dear?! It's me!
Oh, thank god...!
And some demons will appear human.
*Growl*
While some remain as demons.
*Hiss*

*Snicker*
Let us see if who will be able to discern which is which now.
>You see a woman in a state of panic.

*Scream*
Monster!!!
Help me! Someone! Where's Yuichi?! Where's my husband...?!
I'm here! Can't you tell?!

*Scream*
No! Don't come near me!!!
>The female cultist kicks the demon and tries to scamper away.
>The demon gets a hold of her!
Yumi! Yumi, calm down...!

Nooo!
Don't call me that!!
Save the woman.
Attack the demon.
>Your demon acts as a shield for the woman,
>and deflects the demon's attack.
>Your demon attacks the other demon!
*Shriek*
>The demon falls to the floor.
>The female cultist sags to the floor as well.
>You try to lend her a hand but...
No! Monster! Don't come near me!
>She bats your hand away and runs.
>Meanwhile, Vince...
Dammit! The bastard called in all these demons!
We need to deal with the ones around us first!
Honey! You guys! We gotta...!
>He finds himself surrounded by demons.
Where are you guys?! Shit, we already got separated!
M-Monster...!!!
>A panicked cultist with a box cutter attacks Vince.
Hey, calm down! Where the hell did you get that thing?!
The monster's talking... Demon! It's a demon...!!
Alright, time for you to shut up!
Honey! Honey, where'd you go?!
>He sees a woman being attacked by demons.

We need to go!
Come with me!
Outta the way!!
*Moan*
>It's not Honey.
>The girl stares at Vince.
You'll be safe. Just stay behind me, alright?
>Just as the girl turns around,
>something goes crunch and sends a sharp pain throughout his body.
Huh...?
>The girl grins as she presents her bloodstained hands.
>A certain being sits atop the altar looks on in delight.
Humans are powerless in the face of true chaos...

*Snicker*
Weak. So weak.
To be unable to see through even this illusion... This chaos...
Something as simple as making humans appear as demons and vice versa.
Foolish, feeble-minded humans...
I came to teach you the truth behind this universe.
Entertain me. Delight me some more!
>The cultists around the altar are in a frenzied panic.
Reverend, please save us!!

*Scream*
No! Don't come any closer!!
>The leader stabs the demon with the knife that was used for the ritual.

*Scream*
It hurts... It hurts so much...!
*Pant*

What's going on...?
All these monsters...!
Reverend, are you okay?
I think so...
So this is the chaos that an "Outer God" can unleash upon this world...?
We've nearly been killed because of it!
This was not what we hoped for...!
We need to get out of here!
Ah, so some still appear human to you, dear Reverend.
But you may want to worry about how you appear to others.
>Just as Nyarlathotep says that, its appearance begins to warp...

*Snicker*
I am everywhere and nowhere.
This form will do nicely for the time being.
Hey, you okay?! Come on! We gotta get out of here!
>The man snickers as he blends into the crowd...
